What’s it like to have a Lamborghini at 30? Idk I’ll tell you later. 🏎️ #NewGoal
.
The beauty of life is that you are in control. You can live it however you like. 😎

I will keep this up for a few days to save a few college kids from the rat race and anyone that hates their job. I’ve sold this for $15K for the last 3 years. Why? You’ll make way more than that. $15K+ months are normal with a little effort each day. I am feeling extremely grateful today for the life I am currently living. Many will listen and few will apply due to lack of confidence. Let’s begin. ⬇️ 
.
Think of the product/service you want to sell (begin with the end in mind), target that following via location/mindset (fill your list up with all future customers), spoon feed them content you know they’ll like (if you target all investors, they’ll want to hear about investing), launch the project/service and DM everyone that liked any photo on your entire page. Show them something they’ll like more than your content. 
.
Our advertising is amazing because I hand selected everyone. We would be at 8-10K followers if we left “growth” up to chance through content. When other location accounts would pop up, I’d laugh because I know they’d never grow to our level. You need to force it into success or you’ll be spinning your wheels for years.
.
If you are going to run a poll on Instagram, you want to ask a question that will warrant the biggest pool of leads in 24 hours. Then pitch them all the next day: “Thank you for voting on our poll. We saw you were interested in “x”, we’d love to help you out with that or we’d love to show you more info on that.” Never give an option for people to click “no”. That’s a wasted pool. Put: “My friend might be interested.” Not to mention the average person actually gives a shit if the “no” side of the poll is winning. Don’t let the negative perception have a chance of winning by eliminating the option. 
.
See you at the top. 💰

This is how I analyze what accounts are real or fake on Instagram.
.
A restaurant owner in Morristown had a woman with 80K+ followers DEMAND the owner give her and her 3 friends free appetizers, entrees and desserts for 1 post.
.
He sent me the account and I tore her account to shreds with every data point backing it because of socialblade.com. She was a full grown adult as well. (Old enough to know better). I saved them probably $800-$1K worth of food + drinks.
.
A friend of mine that bought accounts from me wanted to buy another account from a stranger in LBI. I helped him understand it was safe to buy from using this tool. He actively has the largest LBI account in the area. He also got it for a steal because I know what everything SHOULD cost by the numbers and suggested a negotiating starting point. The account worth like $8K and he got it for $1500.
.
I’ve saved a lot of people from getting scammed and this is how I’ve been able to use data to sell all the accounts I’ve built like my Montclair, Jersey City, Hoboken, Westfield, Newark, Asbury Park accounts etc. 
.
Sorry in advance for all the cursing. I’m going to make an effort to chill out on that.

Do you know how you learn? I used to feel so annoyed with myself because I learned so differently from everyone else. I would always get yelled at in school for GOING AHEAD. Yet… I NEEDED TO! 🧠 💡
.
”Focus on the topic at hand. We don’t need that right now.” My thought process: “YEAH! You don’t, but I do! I am on topic right now. I need to know what chapter 20 is before I can start chapter 1.” 😵‍💫
.
Nowadays… I don’t compare my learning process to others. There’s no one yellow brick road to successful thinking. Analyze what works for you because that’s all you need. 💯 
.
#LearnHowYouLearn

This is everything I use to network with anyone & gain a high social status. I’ve sold this training for thousands for years and today you’re getting it for free. It’s at 1.25x speed for attention span purposes.
.
Apply these principles. Take some of the tips in this video and test them out. Watch how much your life changes. You will make more friends, you will boost your confidence in social settings, you will get more sales, become a better marketer… you will change your life if you apply yourself. 
.
I used to be shy, quiet and introverted … and I was motivated to change that. If you are in a similar position where all you need to know is HOW TO CHANGE… this is your golden ticket. 
.
Enjoy. 😇

Have you ever heard “it’s not what you say, it’s how you say it?”. It’s so true. If you use the correct body language and tonality, very little will be off limits. But you have to “dance at a 10” first to watch it happen in front of you. 🕺🏻 💃🏻 

The Golden Rule is the principle of treating others as one wants to be treated. ✨ 

#Communication #Sales #Psychology

Did you know that for every follow that accepts you back via follow/unfollow, you receive anywhere from 2-6 follows from their network as well. 👥
.
The moment someone follows you back, you end up on their “recommended” list on their profile. Instagram does this automatically. It’s a great way of tapping into the networks of people that you targeted. Instagram does it for you. 👏🏻
.
#QuickMention #IGGrowthHacks

Did you know that the “Full Name” section on Instagram can be used for SEO purposes? If you only work local, it’ll be better to put the location over your industry name. 
.
I am currently just using the section to identify what I am. (Essentially wasting it). Be careful because you can only change the name twice every 14 days.

48 Laws of Power

“Since honesty rarely strengthens friendship, you may never know how a friend truly feels.”

“Without a worthy opponent, a man or group cannot grow stronger.”

“Never let the presence of enemies upset or distress you — you are far better off with a declared opponent or two than not knowing where your real enemies lie. The man of power welcomes conflict, using enemies to enhance his reputation as a surefooted fighter who can be relied upon in times of uncertainty.”

…”for sometimes any emotion is better than the boredom of security.”

“-a person who cannot control his words shows that he cannot control himself, and is unworthy of respect.” “If you do not break your enemy’s reputation cleverly, you will inadvertently ruin your own.”

“People feel superior to the person whose actions they can predict.”

“By not caring how you are perceived, you let others decide this for you. Be the master of your fate, and also of your reputation.”

“The giving makes it hard for the other person to notice the taking.”

“The best calculation is the absence of calculation. Once you have attained a certain level of recognition, others generally figure that when you do something, it’s for an intelligent reason.”

“Retreat into a fortress and you lose contact with the sources of your power.”

 “Never trust the version that people give of themselves — it is utterly unreliable.”

“If you can get the bird to walk into the cage on its own, it will sing that much more prettily.”

“If you stick to conventional appearances in public few will believe you think differently in private.”

“Of all the disorders of the soul, envy is the only one no one confesses to.”

#48LawsOfPower #RobertGreene
